						<summary>

						<p>West wall of the store room in the Tiruttaḷīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Jaṭāvarmaṉ Vīra Pāṇḍya: Year 10: A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete record is dated in the 10th regnal year, Mithuna 7, Magha-nakshatra. These details are not sufficient for verification.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift made by the <hi rend="italic">mūlaparushai-mahāsabhai</hi> of Tirupputtūr, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Kēraḷaśiṅga-vaḷanāḍu to the deity Sūryadēva of the temple of Tiruttaḷiyāṇḍa-nāyaṉar. A certain Achcha-Sirikaraṇi is referred to as a member of the Kaṉṉaḍiya cavalry group. Probably this person must have come from the Karnāṭaka country. </p>						

						</summary>
